<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Monitor resources usage</b></p><p>If you need to track metrics such as memory, CPU, or thread usage within your application, make sure to use <span class="control">CPU and Memory Live Charts</span>. This tool is useful to get an understanding of your application requirements and how it reacts to certain events in terms of resource consumption.</p><p>From the main menu, select <span class="shortcut">View | Tool windows| Profiler</span>, then right-click the desired process and select <span class="control">CPU and Memory Live Charts</span>.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/cpu-memory-live-charts-1.png" alt="CPU and Memory Live charts showing CPU, memory, and threads usage." style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>